This paper is related to video processing and deep learning, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper proposes a new neural network architecture that combines two approaches, kernel estimation and flow map estimation, which are also commonly studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves spatial transformation, which is a topic commonly studied in the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
